=== 2.5 Activation Functions

An *activation function* introduces non-linearity after a linear transformation, allowing neural networks to model complex relationships.

*ReLU* (Rectified Linear Unit):

stem:[\text{ReLU}(x) = \max(0, x)]

*GELU* (Gaussian Error Linear Unit), used in GPT's feed-forward layers:

stem:[\text{GELU}(x) = x \cdot \Phi(x)]

where stem:[\Phi(x)] is the standard normal CDF.
A fast approximation used in practice:

stem:[\text{GELU}(x) \approx 0.5 x \left(1 + \tanh\!\left(\sqrt{2/\pi}(x + 0.044715 x^3)\right)\right)]

Without activations, stacking linear layers collapses to a single linear transformation — depth would buy nothing.

